    "summary": "Graduated from the National School of Geosciences Applications (ENAG-BRGM, France), I am a Geologist by training. \n\nThroughout my career I learned and developed new skills and my current area of interest is \"Wireline Logging\". In this field, I have now more than six years experience in various domains such as:\n\n\u25ba Geotechnical Engineering\n\u25ba Mineral Exploration\n\u25ba Oil & Gas Exploration\n\u25ba Geothermal Exploration\n\u25ba Hydrogeology\n\nAs a primarily trained Geologist, I also demonstrate other skills in the field of \"Mineral Exploration\" such as:\n\n\u25ba Geological Mapping\n\u25ba Diamond Cores & RC/RAB Cuttings Logging\n\u25ba 3D Modeling & Resource Estimation\n\nFluent in both French and English, I had the chance to work in several places across the World such as Europe, Africa, North America or Asia Pacific, both onshore and offshore. I am therefore accustomed to work in challenging environments and remote places.\n\nMy main motivation is to work, evolve and grow along with professionals from various countries and cultures. I am a detail-oriented and result-driven person, therefore I attached a strong importance to the satisfaction of my clients and my co-workers.\n\nDynamic and proactive, I am currently working as a Geophysicist / Borehole Geophysical Logging Engineer at FUGRO (Marine Site Characterization) in The Netherlands.\n\nI remain at your disposal for any further questions you may have about me.",
