                    "description": "The Borehole Geophysical Logging (BGL) team is part of the Client Deliverables Department (CDD), an entity within Fugro's offshore division. It provides data acquisition, processing, and reporting on offshore geotechnical site investigations for logging  services such as P and S Suspension Logging (PSSL) and Acoustic Borehole Imaging (ABI).\n\nAs Geophysicist within the BGL team, a key component of my position is to perform in-situ data acquisition for our clients, especially for the offshore windfarm market, and provide them with high quality data/deliverables. Another critical aspect of my role is to perform review on factual data reports.\n\nOther duties of my role include:\n\n\u25ba Managing onshore and offshore project teams\n\u25ba Recruitment, training, and development of new personnel\n\u25ba Writing technical documentation and training material",
